description.plain:
The Jonas Brothers are an American pop rock band. Formed in 2005, they have gained popularity from the Disney Channel children’s television network and consists of three brothers from Wyckoff, New Jersey: Kevin Jonas, Joe Jonas and Nick Jonas.

In the summer of 2008 they starred in the Disney Channel Original Movie Camp Rock and its sequel, Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam. They also starred as Kevin, Joe, and Nick Lucas in their own Disney Channel series JONAS, which was later re-branded for its second and last season as Jonas L.A.

In 2008, the group was nominated for the Best New Artist award at the 51st Grammy Awards and won the award for Breakthrough Artist at the American Music Awards. They have sold over eight million albums worldwide.

After a six year hiatus, Jonas Brothers reunited to release their comeback single, “Sucker” in March 2019. They later announced their album of return, Happiness Begins, in April 2019. On May 1st, 2019, they announced their first tour together in nearly a decade, “Happiness Begins Tour”.

description.plain:
“Cool” is the second single released by the Jonas Brothers in 2019, after taking a six-year hiatus. The lyrics contain numerous references to the brothers' personal and professional achievements during their years apart. Reflecting on their individual success, they describe a shared sense of satisfaction and peace of mind.

In the brothers' track descriptions for Apple Music, Nick explained:

This song came towards the end of the writing process. We were trying to write a ballad, actually, but we ended up writing this instead because we all came to the studio feeling very cool that day. Feeling like a million bucks.

The music video for the track has a strong eighties aesthetic.  According to a press release from the band, it’s meant to evoke “1984 Miami” and  “channel the spirit of timeless eighties MTV, in all its decadent glory.” The video features multiple references to previous Jonas Brothers projects, most notably the video for their 2008 hit, “Burnin' Up.”

The track was first introduced to social media via Instagram:

https://www.instagram.com/p/BvwXuKrHJPr/?utm_source=ig_embed

The track was first announced on Twitter on January 13, 2020, and was followed by a teaser on YouTube the following day.

The official music video was released alongside the song. The video stars all three brothers alongside their respective wives. The video also features a cameo appearance from actor Matthew Modine.

“Hesitate” is a romantic track about wanting to help a lover through their burdens. It illustrates a new maturity that the boys possess when it comes to relationships and communication, contrasting their past, frustration-filled breakup songs like “S.O.S.”

According to Billboard, Nick said that this song is Joe’s “love letter” to his then-fiancée, now wife, Sophie Turner. The two got married after the 2019 Billboard Music Awards, and Joe explained to Harper’s Bazaar that they got legally married there, but are planning to have a more formal, “proper” wedding in the future.

description.plain:
The Jonas boys put a fresh spin on the Busted classic.

By covering what could be interpreted as a banal tune the Jonas brothers make an elaborate statement about the state of art. This shifts a fun jam from Busted, into a profound message about the lack of human imagination. By imagining the year 3000 and being thoroughly unable to describe any of the wonders there, the brothers are noting the inability of art provide what Jonathan Lear calls a ‘radical hope’ of a future that is entirely beyond modern cultural constructs.

Some lyrics were changed from the original song to suit JB’s young audience, including:


“And your great, great, great granddaughter is pretty fine” to “and your great, great, great granddaughter is doing fine”
“Triple-breasted women swim around town totally naked” to “girls there with round hair like Star Wars float above the floor”



In addition, the line “it had outsold Michael Jackson” was changed to “it had outsold Kelly Clarkson” to accommodate the charts of the time — at the time of release, some of Kelly’s most recent hits were “Behind These Hazel Eyes” and “Since U Been Gone.”

All of these line changes both serve to make this song family-friendly and to emphasize how little is actually described about the future.

“And your great, great, great granddaughter is pretty fine” to “and your great, great, great granddaughter is doing fine”
“Triple-breasted women swim around town totally naked” to “girls there with round hair like Star Wars float above the floor”



In addition, the line “it had outsold Michael Jackson” was changed to “it had outsold Kelly Clarkson” to accommodate the charts of the time — at the time of release, some of Kelly’s most recent hits were “Behind These Hazel Eyes” and “Since U Been Gone.”

All of these line changes both serve to make this song family-friendly and to emphasize how little is actually described about the future.

“Love Her” is essentially a love letter to the significant others of the band. The song references important sacrifices that are made in a healthy relationship in order to make it work. In some ways, they reference an age-old mantra, “Happy wife, happy life.”

The brothers sing about the difficulties and little arguments that might come up, but the love they feel for their significant other makes all the pain and heartache that can come with a relationship worth it. This track shows growth and maturity in the way the Jonas Brothers approach relationships as grown men rather than the boys who wrote their previous tracks about falling in love and being in a committed relationship.

“LIke It’s Christmas” is obviously a Christmas single from Jonas Brothers, which was released on November 8, 2019. The instrumental consists of bells with upbeat drums, and a repeating acoustic and electric guitar pattern.

On November 1, 2019, exactly a week before the song’s release, the band replied to a fan page account’s tweet, which revealed the artwork of the song, which only showed the brothers' faces. Three days later, on November 4, they announced the song’s title and release date.

A lyric video was published to the band’s YouTube channel on December 6, 2019, which was nineteen days before Christmas.

“Pom Poms” was meant to be the first single from the Jonas Brothers' fifth album, but the project was ultimately cancelled when the group split. It was released on April 2, 2013, through Jonas Brothers Recording.

The lyrics are infamously more sexual in meaning than the Jo Bros' previous work, with pom poms symbolizing parts of a woman’s physique.

The song’s music video concept was dreamed up by Joe Jonas. When Kevin told his wife Danielle about the treatment they had planned, it raised her eyebrow.

Kevin: It opens up on a hot summer day. You see coffee shops, gas stations, a man sitting in his rocking chair. We finally get to an old, broken-down football field, where we find the Jonas Brothers and a few trashy cheerleaders.
Danielle: What does trashy cheerleaders mean?
Kevin: Ugly.

description.plain:
One of Disney Channel favorite couples back in 2007 was Nick Jonas and Miley Cyrus. During their time together they have never confirmed their relationship but it was in late 2007 when they called it off . From being young and in love while being in the eye of the public they’ve never addressed their romance, but after some time apart they reconciled and from that reconciliation the break up diet “ Before The Storm” was born. They wrote the song together and it ended up on the Jonas Brothers 4th studio album “Lines, Vines and Trying Times” which was released June 16th 2009.

From an interview with ENews back on November 27th 2018, Nick said the following:

“‘Before the Storm’ is probably one of my favorite songs on the record,” Nick told MTV News at the time. “I think it’s probably one of my favorite songs because it has a great story to it. It’s a duet with Miley, which is great.”
Nick went on to say he was excited to share the song (and the couple’s story) with the fans, adding, “It’s a good thing that happened and it’ll be a good one to play live.” “

Going forward, Nick Jonas during his solo career alongside his career with his brothers had sang segments of the song and melted it in with medleys from the Jonas Brothers, and it was at the time a huge fan request.

To this date, in a most recent interview accordés to Teen Vogue last March 2019, Nick said the following:
“ […] We had a song with her back in the day called ‘Before the Storm,’ which is my favorite catalogue song of the Jonas Brothers,” he said. “And at that point she was 16 and she was singing her *ss off. So, it’s no surprise now that people are coming around to [her talent]. But I’m sitting around going, ‘Told you so.’” . “

description.plain:
Released for the 2007 Disney film Meet the Robinsons, “Kids of the Future” is a clever rewrite/cover of the 1981 Kim Wilde song “Kids in America”.

Instead of the original song’s emphasis on American youth, this version focuses on the spectacularity of the future and changes the verses to mirror the emotional journey and plot of the movie. The song’s following of the movie’s plot in this manner was also used in a special version of the music video that added in scenes from the movie that matched the verses' lyrics, and that played on Disney Channel during the movie’s promotion.

The song’s subject has lied to the narrator about their sexual health and as a result the narrator feels betrayed and uncomfortable.
